text: Zhejiang is a province in east China. "Zhejiang" is named by the Qiantang River, which is also called "Zhejiang". "Zhejiang" means "bent river". It has a population of more than 64 million people. The capital of Zhejiang Province is Hangzhou. == Political divisions == Zhejiang Province is divided into eleven municipalities (Chinese:地级市). # Hangzhou Municipality # Ningbo Municipality # Huzhou Municipality # Jiaxing Municipality # Jinhua Municipality # Lishui Municipality # Quzhou Municipality # Shaoxing Municipality # Taizhou Municipality # Wenzhou Municipality # Zhoushan Municipality == References ==
